messages.messageBody:
That is creepy. You're just getting linked everywhere now. Could be a good
thing? or not?
tammy

-------Original Message-------

From: AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com
Date: Friday, June 13, 2003 16:08:32
To: AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [AlwaysLearning] creepy interesting link to my site

I accidently typed in google.com instead of sandradodd.com (because my
fingers can type google.com as quickly as they can type albuquerque) and
then I
thought I can still get to my testing page (which is what I wanted).

I threw some words in and got this:

LBE7
. Teaching to a Higher Standard: Forget Standardized ... Service If You
Cannot Avoid Standardized
Tests... ... invalidate the results Sandra Dodd government Washington's ...
www.chemistrycoach.com/lbe7.htm - 68k - Cached - Similar pages

It's a site with HUNDREDS, it seems, of links to stuff about tests, test
design, test prep, and down under "NEWS" (of all things) is a link to my
page on
invalidating tests.

Huh!!

Way near the bottom:
